In [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] law, a '''crime against civilization''' was the greatest crime of war one could be charged with. In a trial for crimes against civilization, the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] would serve as the jury, with the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] serving as the judge.

[[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma]] [[Trial of Ulic Qel-Droma|was tried]] for crimes against civilization for his actions in the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]]. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Kar Vastor]] was charged with crimes against civilization for his role in the [[Battle of Haruun Kal/Legends|Battle of Haruun Kal]], but he apparently did not go to trial for reasons unknown. [[Depa Billaba/Legends|Depa Billaba]] was also supposed to be tried for the same reasons as Vastor, but she went into a coma, thus saving her from trial.

